# Constant Fold CAST/Type Conversions

## Description

Evaluates CAST expressions at compile time when the input is a constant.
CAST('42' AS INTEGER) becomes 42. CAST(3.14 AS TEXT) becomes '3.14'.

**When to apply**: CAST with a constant input value.

**Why it works**: Type conversions on constants can be computed once
at plan time instead of per row.

## Implementation

```rust
rw!("fold-cast";
    "(cast ?val ?type)" => { FoldCast("?val", "?type") }
    if is_const("?val")
),
rw!("fold-redundant-cast";
    "(cast ?val ?type)" => "?val"
    if has_type("?val", "?type")
),
```

## Preconditions

```rust
fn applicable(val: &Expr, target_type: &DataType) -> bool {
    val.is_literal()
    && can_cast(val.data_type(), target_type)
}
```

## Test Cases

```sql
-- Before
SELECT * FROM t WHERE id = CAST('42' AS INTEGER);
-- After
SELECT * FROM t WHERE id = 42;
```

```sql
-- Redundant cast removal
SELECT CAST(42 AS INTEGER) FROM t;
-- After: SELECT 42 FROM t;
```

